(2) Without limiting the generality of subsection (1), the holder of a large-scale mining licence may himself or by his servants and agents— (a) enter on to the mining area and take all reasonable measures on or under the surface for the purpose of mining operations ; (b) erect the necessary equipment, plant and buildings for the purposes of mining , transporting, dressing or treating the mineral recovered in the course of mining operations ; (c) dispose of any mineral product recovered; (d) prospect within the mining area for any mineral ; and (e) stack or dump any mineral or waste products.
